               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-269-person2408">
                  JEREMIAH 
                  McGURRIN
               <interp inst="t18310217-269-person2408" type="surname" value="McGURRIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-269-person2408" type="given" value="JEREMIAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-269-person2408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18310217-269-viclabel1561" type="occupation">keep a beer and porter shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-269-victim2407 t18310217-269-viclabel1561"></join> in Barbican. On the 4th of February I received a sovereign and 2s. 6d. in silver, at Shadwell, in the evening - I then went with two other persons, and had 1 1/2 lb. of steaks, two pots of porter, and three four-penny worths of gin-and-water between us; I then went to another public-house, where I saw the prisoner - she asked me to treat her, which I did; we were there two or three hours - we had about two quarterns of gin, and I had four pennyworth of gin-and-water; I was not drunk - we came together to <placeName id="t18310217-269-crimeloc1562">Red Lion-market, Whitecross-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-269-crimeloc1562" type="placeName" value="Red Lion-market, Whitecross-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-269-crimeloc1562" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-269-off1559 t18310217-269-crimeloc1562"></join>; she followed me nearly to my own house - I had not known her before; I had taken out my bag and paid for the liquor at the public-house - I felt in it a sovereign, and 1s. 6d., and I had 6d. worth of copper in the same pocket - when I got near to Red Lion-market I had occasion to stop; I took my bag from my right-hand breeches pocket, and thrust it into my bosom for safety, as I thought the prisoner followed me too long; no sooner had I done that than she snatched the bag from my bosom, and ran away - I sung out Stop thief! she ran out of the market; I made a rush to catch her, and fell on my knees - she ran out, but came into the market again, and the Policeman took her; he found on her my pocket handkerchief, but none of the money, nor the bag - I was sober, and I swear she took it from me; I did not like her being so long about me, and wanted to get from her; I am married.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-269-person2409">
                  GEORGE 
                  GLADWELL
               <interp inst="t18310217-269-person2409" type="surname" value="GLADWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-269-person2409" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-269-person2409" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I heard the alarm, and saw the prisoner run about twenty yards before I caught her; the prosecutor said she had robbed him of a sovereign, and a bag - the flap of his breeches was undone, and the knees muddy: I found the handkerchief on the prisoner, a sixpence, and 4d. in copper; the prosecutor was the worse for liquor, but not drunk.</p>
               <p>JEREMIAH McGURRIN. This handkerchief was in my coat pocket - I did not give it to her.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written defence, stating that the prosecutor, who was intoxicated, had followed her, endeavouring to prevail on her to accompany him, but that she had not robbed him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310217-269-verdict1563" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310217-269-verdict1563" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-269-verdict1563" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               GUILTY of stealing the handkerchief
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310217-269-punish1564" type="punishmentDescription">
